16:
The great dragon has passed on.
Despite the rude interruption...
19:
He met his end with dignity and
grace. We needn't lament his
passing.
21:
Won't the forest lose its protection
without his powers?
24:
Our days of hiding away are over.
We should count this as a blessing,
for now we can act before regret
takes us.
28:
As so it happens, we even have the
opportunity to join hands with
worthy allies.
33:
Now then. I accept your proposed
alliance.
40:
You heard me. From today onward,
man and elf shall walk together
toward a new future.
47: What is it you take issue with?
50:
I just could not help but wonder if
such a monumental decision should
be made by only one person.
53:
What, is the word of one little girl not
good enough?
57:
It is not your lack of age that I find
issue with.
60:
Good. But I'll have you know that I'm
not THAT young. I'm already thirteen.
66:
You're YOUNGER than me?! But
you're... so mature...
70: People like her usually have to be.
74:
There is no one else that would lead
the elves in my stead. The others are
all lost in a dream.
77:
You can wake them if you want, but
I'd rather spare us from their out of
touch opinions. The barrier is going
to fall, whether they like it or not.
81:
If you are truly the sole speaker for
your people, then let our alliance be
forged.
85:
I express my sincerest gratitude
both to our new allies, and to the
greater powers which smile upon
our union.
88:
...Hm. The protective barrier won't
last much longer.
91:
But the Mark could be used to
restore it. Should man and elf wish
to hide in the forest, we could waste
away our days in peace.
95:
Hey. That's not for you to decide. The
thing's meant for Light, isn't it?
99:
Rustamov waited just to give it to
him.
103:
Nimbus is right. Rustamov entrusted
his life to... To the Champion.
105:
...And as the bearer of that mantle, I
must see its duties fulfilled.
112: I agree. The Mark should go to them.
114:
Let us reclaim everything that was
taken from us...
118:
Including Excelion. It shall be ours
once more!
128:
May its blessing, gentle and
comforting, rouse you from your
slumber. It is time, child of the stars.
129:
Awaken, to the refrain of eternal
love. Awaken, to the light's enduring
chorus. It is time.
135:
As you should. The first elves
opened their eyes in Starview
Village.
136:
Among the many legends the high
elves left us, the one we never forgot
was of Starview's goddess.
138:
Gentle and comforting, befitting of
the stars was she who made us.
144:
I'm sure none of this comes as a
surprise.
147:
What you've described has
appeared to me in a dream before.
Inside it, I spoke with someone
resembling Light...
150:
I said something which saddened
him, but I can't remember what. I
struggle to recall details, despite
being there.
152:
It's as if something inside me is
missing.
156:
The truth is that there is another
Stella—the goddess of death and
destruction who brought forth the
Lord of Shadow.
158:
But if you wish to learn any more,
you'll have to question her yourself.
161: Then that is what I must do.
168:
Sorry, I couldn't help myself. A
thought came to me, you see.
170:
I never would've expected our
mother to be so imperfect, but my
love for her is no less diminished
because of her faults.
173:
Speaking of imperfections... You,
leader of men.
177:
I had assumed you would've asked
to fix the barrier, and yet you did not.
179:
Do you desire to rise beyond only
ensuring your people's safety?
186:
There are other duties I must fulfill if I
am to be a worthy ruler!
189:
Is that so? Then I shall question you
no further.
193:
As for your march on Excelion, I'll
lend you my aid.
195:
We leaders need to band together
during these trying times. Don't we,
Lilith Stratos?
200: She is a frightening one, isn't she?
204: Is that how you saw her?
208:
Surely you noticed how perceptive
she was. Doesn't it make you uneasy
to be so exposed?
210:
In any case, I apologize for
interfering. I hope you rest well
tonight. Tomorrow is looking to be a
long day.
